column2: Sunny after 5-6 days of rain. breeze
Cool breeze; air temp 55 degrees; rained for past 3 days
Beautiful day; starting to warm slightly; a little more cloudy at 2: 00
Three days windy and clear since flood waters were at crest.
Algae levels increasing and in some back areas are bad looking- most areas are just slightly impaired.
Some algae but beautiful- calm day with good sun
Slight overcast- cooler weather all day rain over inch yesterday.  Some really green stuff in some of the bays.
Slight breeze- but beautiful day - no rain or storms for several days.
People enjoying the beach and fishing- some breeze- water temp is near 70 degrees.
It has been real hot for 2 weeks- the upper part of flowage really getting good algae bloom.  Nice sunny day today- little wind.
Improvement over the 24th + 4th of July.  It was very bad then.  Some rain lately.
Partly cloudy- very calm- swimming class enjoying the lake- some green but much better than the 4th of July
Pretty good swimming conditions- but still a lot of algae.  When it rains the dam opens and worse stuff moves out.  No rain and algae builds up.
Slight haze- not a lot of algae
Bad algae bloom still on the jump river.  Our winds have been from the west and south and holding the stuff up there.  The Chippewa's heavy flow clears quickly.
Wet all labor weekend but no big storms
Floods last week May have stained water more than usual.  No algae.
No algae but water is a little darker than usual- possibly because of flood in north 2 weeks ago.  Not too sunny- only 48 degrees today
Cool.  Assumed 12: 30 for sample time.  No card
The last 5 days it has been 95 degrees.
A very nice day after a big weekend with a cool down after 2 weeks of 92-96 degrees.
Plenty of rain and drawing down- leaves in our area are pretty nice.  Upper end of lake on jump river is much more green.
A lot of rain this last week.
Cool off and no rain for a few days.
Green scum on the lake- many floating logs and debris.
Some algae.  Current was strong- wind picking up.
Heavy rain the night before last- algae apparent.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 3'.
Rained last night- and water got a little choppy- algae level not as high as usual at this date
Algae level increasing on south of lake due to wind.
Rained about 1 1/2 inches yesterday. Some algal bloom.  Thermometer was turned. Changed profile data to 22 C- not 17 C.
No rain in the last week. Algae bloom.
1.5 inches rain last 5 days - not as green as last month.
Breezy- cool- partly cloudy.  Emily Lind trained me on how to measure Secchi and take chemical samples.  Several eagles were observed in the area.
Partly cloudy- wind 5 mph- 61 degrees.  quiet with no boat traffic.
Sunny- 4-5 mph breeze- light boat traffic- 68 degrees
